Live from Death Row , published in May 1995 , is a collection of memoirs by American former death row inmate Mumia Abu - Jamal .
Professor Palmboom ( literally translated as Professor Palm Tree ) is a comic album series written and drawn by Dutch artist Dick Briel .
Yawara ! ( also stylized as YAWARA ! ) is a Japanese manga series by Naoki Urasawa which ran in Big Comic Spirits from 1986 to 1993 .
Honoré de Balzac 's Splendeurs et misères des courtisanes , translated either as The Splendors and Miseries of Courtesans or as A Harlot High and Low , was published in four parts from 1838 - 1847 .
`` The Beast in the Cave '' is a short story by American horror fiction writer H. P. Lovecraft .
The Common Sense Book of Baby and Child Care written by Benjamin Spock , is a manual on infant and child care first published in 1946 .
What Mad Universe is a science fiction novel , written in 1949 by the American author , Fredric Brown .
`` A Child in the Dark , and a Foreign Father '' is a short story written by the iconic Australian writer and poet , Henry Lawson .
The Horatians and the Curiatians ( Die Horatier und die Kuriatier ) is a Lehrstück ( `` Schulstück '' in the collected plays ) by the German dramatist Bertolt Brecht written in collaboration with Margarete Steffin in 1933 - -34 .
Flaubert 's Parrot is a novel by Julian Barnes that was shortlisted for the Booker Prize in 1984 and won the Geoffrey Faber Memorial Prize the following year .
A Case of Two Cities is Qiu Xiaolong 's fourth Inspector Chen novel ( after 2004 's When Red Is Black ) .
Put Down Your Whip , also translated as Lay Down Your Whip ( Chinese : 放下你的鞭子 ; pinyin : Fàngxià nǐde biānzi ) , was a 1931 Chinese street play written by Chen Liting during the Republican era , who drew inspiration from the earlier play Meiniang by Tian Han .
Dear Daddy is a 1976 play written by English playwright Denis Cannan , first staged at the Ambassadors Theatre in London 's West End .
Mindbend is a novel by the author Robin Cook , first published in 1985 .
The Care of Time ( 1981 ) is the last novel by British spy fiction writer Eric Ambler .
My Night with Reg is a play by British playwright Kevin Elyot which was produced in 1994 by the Royal Court Theatre , London , directed by Roger Michell .
The Need for Roots : prelude towards a declaration of duties towards mankind ( French : L'Enracinement , prélude à une déclaration des devoirs envers l'être humain ) is a book by Simone Weil .
The Unholy Pilgrim is a historical novel , written by R.F. Tapsell and published in 1968 , which is set in turbulent 13th - century Europe during the High Middle Ages , and follows the adventures of Tancred of Varville .
Studies from an Eastern Home ( 1913 ) is an autobiographical book written by Sister Nivedita .
The Country of the Pointed Firs is an 1896 short story sequence by Sarah Orne Jewett which is considered by some literary critics to be her finest work .
My Real Children is a 2014 alternate history novel by Jo Walton , published by Tor Books .
Between Past and Future is book written by German philosopher Hannah Arendt .
`` The Ghost of the Grotto '' is a 26-page funny animal comic book story written , drawn , and lettered by Carl Barks .
Charity Girl is a Regency romance novel by Georgette Heyer , first published in 1970 .
Planet Tad is a 2012 comedic children 's novel by Tim Carvell .
End the Fed is a 2009 book by Congressman Ron Paul of Texas .
Fabulous Nobodies is the first novel by Australian author and fashion journalist Lee Tulloch .
The Crossover is a 2014 children 's book by American author Kwame Alexander and the winner of the 2015 Newbery Medal and Coretta Scott King Award Honor .
Den sista cigaretten ( lit . The Last Cigarette ) is the twelfth novel by Swedish author Klas Östergren .
Loranga , Masarin och Dartanjang is a Swedish children 's fiction book written by Barbro Lindgren and published in 1969 .
The Last Templar is a 2005 novel by Raymond Khoury , and also is his debut work .
The Bathhouse ( Баня , Banya ) is a play by Vladimir Mayakovsky written in 1929 , for the Meyerhold Theatre .
The Red Napoleon ( 1929 ) is a novel by Floyd Gibbons predicting a Soviet conquest of Europe and invasion of America .
King Lear is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare .
The Water of the Hills ( L'eau des Collines ) is the collective name for two novels by Marcel Pagnol .
Muddle Earth is a children 's novel by Paul Stewart , published in 2003 , and illustrated by Chris Riddell .
Madeline and the Bad Hat is an illustrated children 's novel by Ludwig Bemelmans featuring the popular children 's character Madeline .
The Colonizer and the Colonized ( French : Portrait du colonisé , précédé par Portrait du colonisateur ) is a well - known nonfiction book of Albert Memmi , published in French in 1957 and in English at first in 1965 .
Social Theory and Social Structure ( STSS ) was a landmark publication in sociology by Robert K. Merton .
The Loveday Loyalty is the seventh book in the Loveday series written by Kate Tremayne .
Fine Clothes to the Jew is a 1927 poetry collection by Langston Hughes published by Alfred A. Knopf .
The Man Who Smiled ( original : Mannen som log ) is a novel by Swedish crime - writer Henning Mankell , and is the fourth in the Inspector Wallander series , although the English translations have not been published in chronological order .
The Utopian language is the language of the fictional land of Utopia , as described in Thomas More 's Utopia .
The Secret Intensity of Everyday Life is a novel by the British playwright , novelist and Oscar nominated screenwriter William Nicholson .
Diary of a Bad Year is a book by South African - born Nobel laureate J. M. Coetzee .
The Legacy of Luna is a book written by Julia Butterfly Hill about her experiences while protecting a tree named Luna .
The Boy Who Lost His Face ( ISBN 0 - 679 - 88622 - 2 ) is a novel by Louis Sachar .
I Hate Hamlet is a comedy - drama written in 1991 by Paul Rudnick .
Driving Like Crazy is a 2009 book by P. J. O'Rourke about the automobile .
`` The Red Peri '' is a science fiction novella by Stanley G. Weinbaum that first appeared in the November 1935 issue of Astounding Stories .
Kvachi Kvachantiradze ( Georgian : ) is a novel written by Mikheil Javakhishvili in 1924 .
One of the Family ( 1993 ) was the last novel written by Monica Dickens , great granddaughter of Charles Dickens .
Lady Oracle is a novel by Margaret Atwood that parodies Gothic romances and fairy tales .
The Rules of Survival ( 2006 ) , is a novel by Nancy Werlin .
Back to the Moon was Homer Hickam 's first book - length fiction , published in June 1999 .
Daughter of Fortune ( original Spanish title Hija de la fortuna ) is a novel by Isabel Allende , and was chosen as an Oprah 's Book Club selection in February 2000 .
The Wee Free Men is a 2003 comic fantasy novel by Terry Pratchett , which takes place in his Discworld setting .
The Nightly News is a six - issue American comic book limited series written and drawn by Jonathan Hickman and published by Image Comics .
Post Oaks & Sand Roughs is a semi - autobiographical adventure novel by Robert E. Howard .
Political Fictions is a 2001 book of essays by Joan Didion on the American political process .
Ailleurs are the transcripts of a series of interviews between Jean - Louis Ezine and the French Nobel laureate J. M. G. Le Clézio .
Le Livre des fuites was written in French by French Nobel laureate writer J. M. G. Le Clézio and translated into English as The Book of Flights :
Pretty Little Mistakes is a book written by Heather McElhatton and published on May 1 , 2007 by HarperCollins .
Dr. Adder is a dark science fiction novel by K. W. Jeter set in a future where the United States has largely broken down into reluctantly cooperating enclaves run by a wide variety of strongmen and warlords , with a veneer of government control that seems largely interested in controlling technology .
White Buildings was the first collection ( 1926 ) of poetry by Hart Crane , an American modernist poet , critical to both lyrical and language poetic traditions .
English Passengers ( ISBN 0 - 385 - 49744-X ) is a 2000 historical novel written by Matthew Kneale , which won that year 's Whitbread Book Award and was shortlisted for the Booker Prize and the Miles Franklin Award .
Ramona is an 1884 American novel written by Helen Hunt Jackson .
`` The Mad Moon '' is a science fiction short story by Stanley G. Weinbaum , first published in the December 1935 issue of Astounding Stories .
Alexandr v tramvaji is one of the best - known works of author Pavel Řezníček .
Into the Slave Nebula is a science fiction novel written by John Brunner and first published in 1968 .
The Waste Land is a long poem by T. S. Eliot .
Éloa , ou La sœur des anges ( Éloa , or the Sister of the Angels ) , published in 1824 ( see 1824 in poetry ) , is Alfred de Vigny 's epic tripartite philosophic poem of Eloa , an innocent angel who falls in love with a stranger at odds with God .
The Case of Sergeant Grischa ( 1927 ) is a war novel by the German writer Arnold Zweig .
Salvation on Sand Mountain is a 1995 non - fiction book by Dennis Covington .
The Dastard is the twenty - fourth book of the Xanth series by Piers Anthony .
Entdeckung der blauen Grotte auf der Insel Capri ( Discovery of the Blue Grotto on the Isle of Capri ) is an 1838 book by German writer and painter August Kopisch in which he describes his 1826 rediscovery of the Blue Grotto in Capri together with his friend Ernest Fries .
ODTAA ( 1926 ) by John Masefield ( 1878 - -1967 ) is an adventure novel first published in February 1926 .
Uusi Runo is a 1943 poetry collection by Finnish poet Aaro Hellaakoski .
The Miracle of the Rose ( in French : Miracle de la rose ) is a 1946 book by Jean Genet about experiences as a detainee in Mettray Penal Colony and Fontevrault prison - although there is no direct evidence of Genet ever having been imprisoned in the latter establishment .
Here Be Dragons is a historical novel written by Sharon Kay Penman published in 1985 .
The Fifth Sacred Thing is a 1993 post - apocalyptic novel written by Starhawk .
The Prince ( Italian : Il Principe ( il ˈprintʃipe ) ) is a 16th - century political treatise by the Italian diplomat and political theorist Niccolò Machiavelli .
Dibs in Search of Self is a book by clinical psychologist and author Virginia Axline published in 1964 .
A Plea for Captain John Brown is an essay by Henry David Thoreau .
Supreme Courtship is a 2008 novel by Christopher Buckley , which tells the story of a Judge Judy - style TV judge nominated to the Supreme Court of the United States .
Scepticism and Animal Faith ( 1923 ) is a later work by Spanish - born American philosopher George Santayana .
High Brows is a 1929 novel by Scottish writer Bruce Marshall .
Executive Power is Vince Flynn 's fifth novel , and the fourth to feature Mitch Rapp , an American agent that works for the CIA as an operative for a covert counter terrorism unit called the `` Orion Team . ''
The Prose Works , or Prose Works Other than Science and Health , is a single - volume compendium of the key works of Mary Baker Eddy , the founder of Christian Science , outside of its denominational textbook .
The Surrogates is a five - issue comic book limited series written by Robert Venditti , drawn by Brett Weldele , and published by Top Shelf Productions from 2005 to 2006 .
`` A Winter amid the Ice '' ( French : Un hivernage dans les glaces ) is an 1855 short adventure story by Jules Verne .
Doctor Wortle 's School , alternatively Dr. Wortle 's School or Dr Wortle 's School , published in 1881 , is a novel by Anthony Trollope , his fortieth book .
Henry and the Paper Route is a book that was written by Beverly Cleary and illustrated by Louis Darling .
Anatomy of Gray is a play by Jim Leonard set in the 1880s .
The Geographica ( Ancient Greek : Γεωγραφικά Geōgraphiká ) , or Geography , is an encyclopedia of geographical knowledge , consisting of 17 ' books ' , written in Greek by Strabo , an educated citizen of the Roman empire of Greek descent .
Young Lonigan is a 1932 novel by James T. Farrell .
The Women 's History of the World ( ISBN 0 - 586 - 08886 - 5 ) is a book about women 's history written by British author Rosalind Miles and first published in 1988 .
Everyone Says Hello is a BBC Audiobooks original audiobook written by Dan Abnett and based on the British science fiction television , Doctor Who spin - off series Torchwood .
The Lad and the Lion is an adventure novel by Edgar Rice Burroughs , written in February 1914 .
Paper Lion is a 1966 non - fiction book by American author George Plimpton .
The Zürau Aphorisms ( German : Die Zürauer Aphorismen ) are 109 aphorisms of Franz Kafka , written from September 1917 to April 1918 and published by his friend Max Brod in 1931 , after his death .
Return of the Sorceress is a fantasy novel by Tim Waggoner published in November 2004 , and set in the world of Dragonlance , and based on the Dungeons & Dragons role - playing game .
Adolphe is a classic French novel by Benjamin Constant , first published in 1816 .
Walking to Babylon is a 1998 novel by Kate Orman in the Virgin New Adventures series featuring the fictional archaeologist Bernice Summerfield ( known as Benny ) .
`` I Kissed a Girl '' is a song recorded by American singer Katy Perry for her second studio album , One of the Boys ( 2008 ) .
The Abbreviacion of Statutis ( 1519 ) , of which fifteen editions appeared before 1625 , is a book by John Rastell .
The Return of the Native is Thomas Hardy 's sixth published novel .
Slapping the Table in Amazement ( Chinese : 初刻拍案驚奇 ) is a collection of vernacular short stories , written by Ling Mengchu ( 1580 - -1644 ) .
See You Tomorrow is a critically acclaimed novel by Norwegian author Tore Renberg .
Henry IV , Part 2 is a history play by William Shakespeare , believed written between 1596 and 1599 .
Questions of Travel is a 2012 novel by Australian author Michelle de Kretser .
The Letters of J. R. R. Tolkien ( ISBN 0 - 618 - 05699 - 8 ) is a selection of J. R. R. Tolkien 's letters published in 1981 , edited by Tolkien 's biographer Humphrey Carpenter assisted by Christopher Tolkien .
The Towers of Trebizond is a novel by Rose Macaulay ( 1881 - -1958 ) .
Prison Memoirs of an Anarchist is Alexander Berkman 's account of his experience in prison in Western Penitentiary of Pennsylvania , in Pittsburgh , from 1892 to 1906 .
Hotel World is a postmodern novel , influenced by modernist novels , written by Ali Smith .
`` Miss Temptation '' is a short story written by Kurt Vonnegut , published in The Saturday Evening Post in 1956 .
The Jessica Darling books are a The New York Times bestselling series of five young adult novels by Megan McCafferty , published between 2001 and 2009 .
Captain Pugwash is a fictional pirate in a series of British children 's comic strips and books created by John Ryan .
Armageddon 's Children is the first novel in Terry Brooks ' fantasy trilogy The Genesis of Shannara , which bridges the events of Brooks ' Word and Void trilogy with his Shannara series .
Scottish Folk Tales is a 1976 anthology of 18 fairy tales from Scotland that have been collected and retold by Ruth Manning - Sanders .
Kissing the Gunner 's Daughter is a 1992 novel by the British mystery writer Ruth Rendell , featuring the recurring character Inspector Reg Wexford .
Betelguese , a Trip Through Hell is a 1908 lyrical poem book written by Jean Louis De Esque .
`` Triumphs of a Taxidermist '' is an 1894 short story by British writer H. G. Wells .
The House of Silk is a Sherlock Holmes novel written by British author Anthony Horowitz , published on 1 November 2011 in the United States and Europe .
Bazaar - e - Husn ( Urdu : بازارٍ حسن‎ ) or Seva Sadan ( Hindi : सेवासदन ) is a Hindustani novel by Munshi Premchand .
The Pro Tito Annio Milone ad iudicem oratio ( Pro Milone ) is a speech made by Marcus Tullius Cicero on behalf of his friend Titus Annius Milo .
The Sunne in Splendour is a historical novel written by Sharon Kay Penman .
`` The Crate '' is a short story by Stephen King , first published in the July 1979 issue of Gallery .
Bridge of Scarlet Leaves is a 2012 novel by Kristina McMorris , set during the Japanese American internment of World War II . McMorris has stated that she was inspired to write the book due to her own mixed heritage and decided to call the book Bridge of Scarlet Leaves after reading a Japanese haiku .
Death to the French is a 1932 novel of the Peninsular War during the Napoleonic Wars , written by C. S. Forester , the author of the Horatio Hornblower novels .
The Plains of Passage is an historical fiction novel by Jean M. Auel published in 1990 .
Castle Richmond is the third of five novels set in Ireland by Anthony Trollope .
Diaries of an Internet Lover is a book by TV Presenter and Journalist Dawn Porter .
Eye of the Needle is a spy thriller novel written by Welsh author Ken Follett .
Mistr Kampanus ( román ) is a Czech history novel , written by Zikmund Winter .
Memories of My Melancholy Whores ( Spanish : Memoria de mis putas tristes ) is a novella by Gabriel García Márquez .
Myths and Legends of Babylonia and Assyria is a book by Donald Alexander Mackenzie published in 1915 .
Blaze of Silver is a 2007 young adult historical novel by K M Grant and the final book in the De Granville Trilogy .
Mistress Nell Gwyn is the title of the New York edition of an historical novel by the British writer Marjorie Bowen .
Practical Mysticism is a book written by Evelyn Underhill and first published in 1915 .
Muslims believe the Quran was verbally revealed by God to Muhammad through the angel Gabriel ( Jibril ) , gradually over a period of approximately 23 years , beginning on 22 December 609 CE , when Muhammad was 40 , and concluding in 632 , the year of his death .
Perebendya ( Ukrainian : Перебендя ) is a poem by Taras Shevchenko about the blind itinerant Ukrainian bard ( Kobzar ) .
The Turn of the Screw , originally published in 1898 , is a gothic ghost story novella written by Henry James .
Line War is a 2008 science fiction novel by Neal Asher .
Memories of the Ford Administration is a 1992 novel by John Updike published by Knopf .
Brother Fish is a novel written by Bryce Courtenay that was published in 2004 .
The Pork Butcher is a novel by English writer David Hughes , first published in 1984 , and winner of the 1984 Welsh Arts council prize and the 1985 WH Smith Literary Award .
True Devotion to Mary is a book by Saint Louis de Montfort on the Roman Catholic theme of devotion to the Blessed Virgin Mary .
A Small Place in Italy is a travel memoir and autobiographical novel written by Eric Newby , author of The Last Grain Race and Slowly Down the Ganges .
The Island of the Colorblind is a book by neurologist Oliver Sacks about achromatopsia on the Micronesian atoll of Pingelap .
Peter Pan in Kensington Gardens is a novel by J. M. Barrie , published in 1906 ; it is one of four major literary works by Barrie featuring the widely known literary character he created , Peter Pan .
Be More Chill is a science fiction novel published in 2004 by American author Ned Vizzini .
Torch Song Trilogy is a collection of three plays by Harvey Fierstein rendered in three acts :
Kulliyaat - e - Jamal ( Urdu : کُلیاتِ جمال‎ ) is a collection of complete poetry work by Jamal Ehsani , a Pakistani poet .
Volume Two , Into the Sun & Other Stories is a collection of science fiction short stories by Robert Duncan Milne and edited by Sam Moskowitz .
My Heart 's in the Highlands is a 1789 song and poem by Robert Burns sung to the tune Failte na Miosg .
Confessions of an Actor is Laurence Olivier 's autobiography .
`` A Dynamical Theory of the Electromagnetic Field '' is the third of James Clerk Maxwell 's papers regarding electromagnetism , published in 1865 .
A Crazy Occupation is a memoir by Australian journalist Jamie Tarabay , describing her experience as a foreign correspondent for the Associated Press during the Second Intifada .
The Baritone Wore Chiffon is the second book in Mark Schweizer 's St. Germaine mystery series .
Podkayne of Mars is a science fiction novel by Robert A. Heinlein , originally serialised in Worlds of If ( November 1962 , January , March 1963 ) , and published in hardcover in 1963 .
The Cat 's Quizzer is a children 's book written and illustrated by Theodor Geisel under the pen name Dr. Seuss and published by Random House on August 12 , 1976 .
The Caryatids is a science fiction novel by American writer Bruce Sterling , published in 2009 .
`` Little Bear Bongo '' is a children 's story written by Sinclair Lewis .
Polaroids from the Dead is a collection of short stories and essays by Douglas Coupland .
Love Is ... is the name of a comic strip created by New Zealand cartoonist Kim Casali ( née Grove ) in the 1960s .
Bush in Babylon is a book by the historian Tariq Ali , that attacks the 2003 invasion of Iraq .
The Unicorn Series is a young - adult fantasy novel series by Tanith Lee .
Anthills of the Savannah is a 1987 novel by Nigerian writer Chinua Achebe .
Road Hogs was written by Erick Wujcik , and was published by Palladium Books in 1987 as a 48-page book .
An Indian Study of Love and Death ( 1908 ) is a book written by Sister Nivedita .
The Girl from Hollywood is an Edgar Rice Burroughs contemporary fiction novel .
`` Ole Lukøje '' ( Danish : Ole Lukøje ) is a literary fairy tale by Hans Christian Andersen based upon a folk tale telling of a mysterious mythic creature of the Sandman who gently takes children to sleep and , depending on how good or bad they were , shows them various dreams .
Florentine Histories ( Italian : Istorie fiorentine ) is a historical account by Italian Renaissance political philosopher and writer Niccolò Machiavelli , first published posthumously in 1532 .
The Coming of the Terraphiles is a Doctor Who novel written by Michael Moorcock , featuring the Eleventh Doctor and Amy Pond .
Fascism Viewed from the Right is a book by Italian esoteric writer Julius Evola about the Fascist movement of Italy .
The Reivers , published in 1962 , is the last novel by the American author William Faulkner .
Captain Jan ( Dutch : Hollands Glorie ) is a 1940 novel by Dutch writer Jan de Hartog .
Hole in My Life is an American autobiography of Jack Gantos and was published by Macmillan Publishers in 2002 .
Political Order in Changing Societies is a 1968 book by Samuel P. Huntington dealing with changes in political systems and political institutions .
Diary of a Wimpy Kid is a satirical realistic fiction novel by Jeff Kinney .
If Only It Were True ( original title : Et si c'etait vrai ... ) is French author Marc Levy 's first novel , released in 1999 .
My Philosophical Development is a book written by Bertrand Russell summing up his philosophical beliefs and how they changed during his life .
The World Factbook ( ISSN 1553 - 8133 ; also known as the CIA World Factbook ) is a reference resource produced by the Central Intelligence Agency with almanac - style information about the countries of the world .
The Screwtape Letters is a Christian apologetic novel by C. S. Lewis .
The Wrench , published in the US under the title of The Monkey 's Wrench , was one of Primo Levi 's collections of stories ( another being The Periodic Table ) .
The Moneychangers is a 1975 novel written by Arthur Hailey .
The Reason for God ( 2008 ) is a book and DVD on Christian apologetics by Timothy J. Keller , a scholar and founding of Redeemer Presbyterian Church in New York City .
The Formation of the Economic Thought of Karl Marx : 1843 to Capital ( French : La formation de la pensée économique de Karl Marx : de 1843 à la rédaction du `` Capital '' ) is a 1967 book about the economic theories of Karl Marx by Ernest Mandel .
Brotherband is a series of fantasy novels written by Australian author John Flanagan .
A Foreign Woman ( Russian : Иностранка ) is a novel by the Russian writer Sergei Dovlatov .
Three Dialogues between Hylas and Philonous is a book written by George Berkeley in 1713 .
Executive Order 10925 , signed by President John F. Kennedy on March 6 , 1961 , required government contractors to `` take affirmative action to ensure that applicants are employed and that employees are treated during employment without regard to their race , creed , color , or national origin . ''
The Two Georges is an alternate history novel co - written by science fiction author Harry Turtledove and Oscar - winning actor Richard Dreyfuss .
Les Vingt et un Jours d'un neurasthénique is an expressionist novel by the French writer Octave Mirbeau , published by Charpentier - Fasquelle in August 1901 .
Pnin ( Russian pronunciation : ( pnjin ) ) is Vladimir Nabokov 's 13th novel and his fourth written in English ; it was published in 1957 .
The Kew Letters ( also known as the Circular Note of Kew ) were a number of letters , written by stadtholder William V , Prince of Orange between 30 January and 8 February 1795 from the `` Dutch House '' at Kew Palace , where he temporarily stayed after his flight to England on 18 January 1795 .
Random Acts of Senseless Violence is a dystopian and speculative fiction novel by Jack Womack .
The Blackstone Chronicles is a serialized novel by American horror and suspense author John Saul .
The Soul of the Robot is the sixth science fiction novel by Barrington J. Bayley , featuring the character Jasperodus from his 1956 story `` Fugitive '' .
Published in 2004 by Penguin Books , Adrian Mole and the Weapons of Mass Destruction is Sue Townsend 's sixth full Adrian Mole novel ( as opposed to and the Small Amphibians and the Guardian serial ) .
Send Him Victorious is a political thriller , written in 1968 by Andrew Osmond ( a former officer of Gurkha troops and diplomat ) and Douglas Hurd ( another former diplomat who later became a MP and Cabinet minister .
Disney Fairies debuted September 2005 , when Disney Publishing Worldwide unveiled the novel Fairy Dust and the Quest for the Egg , written by Newbery Honor - winning author Gail Carson Levine with a US$ 1 million marketing and publicity campaign and a virtual world .
Moonlight on the Avenue of Faith is the second novel from Gina B. Nahai and follows the story of Lili and her mother 's mysterious disappearance .
1080 recetas de cocina ( English title : 1080 Recipes ) is a 1972 Spanish cookbook written by Spanish food writer Simone Ortega and published by Alianza Editorial ; it has since been updated and maintained by Ortega and her daughter Inés .
In Praise of Hard Industries is a book about the economic impact of fewer manufacturing jobs in the United States written by Irish journalist and author Eamonn Fingleton .
The Courageous Turk , or Amurath I is a play by the Jacobean dramatist Thomas Goffe , first performed in 1618 and published posthumously in 1632 .
`` Studio 5 , The Stars '' is a short story by British author J. G. Ballard , first appearing in the February 1961 edition of Science Fantasy ( Volume 15 , Number 43 ) ; it was reprinted in the collection Billennium the following year .
Slow Learner is the 1984 published collection of five early short stories by the American novelist Thomas Pynchon , originally published in various sources between 1959 and 1964 .
Flynn of the Inland is a biography by Ion Idriess of John Flynn , founder of the Royal Flying Doctors service .
The Gospel According to Larry is a `` coming of age '' political , romantic teen novel by Janet Tashjian that explores anti - consumerism .
Mimì Bluette ... fiore del mio giardino ( Mimì Bluette ... flower of my garden ) is a novel written by Guido da Verona in 1918 .
Man Descending is a collection of short stories written by Saskatchewan - born writer Guy Vanderhaeghe .
Sketches of Rome is Apollon Maykov 's second book of poetry , published in 1847 .
The Death Gate Cycle is a seven - part series ( heptalogy ) of fantasy novels written by Margaret Weis and Tracy Hickman .
The Society of the Spectacle ( French : La société du spectacle ) is a 1967 work of philosophy and Marxist critical theory by Guy Debord .
The Sexual Life of Catherine M. by the art critic Catherine Millet was published in the author 's native French in 2001 .
A Mirror for Witches is a 1928 novel by American author Esther Forbes , dealing with the witch hunt in 17th Century New England .
Towards the Last Spike was written in 1952 by Canadian poet E. J. Pratt .
Psychoshop is a science fiction novel begun by Alfred Bester , who died in 1987 , and finished by Roger Zelazny .
Rhondda Roundabout ( 1934 ) was the first published novel by the Welsh writer Jack Jones .
The Watertower is a 1994 young adult 's picture book written by Australian author Gary Crew and illustrated by Steven Woolman .
Child Whispers ( published in 1922 ) is the first published work of the English children 's author Enid Blyton , illustrated by her childhood friend and collaborator Phyllis Chase .
A Leaf in the Storm , a Novel of War - Swept China is a 1941 novel by Lin Yutang , in effect a sequel to his Moment in Peking .
Isaac 's Universe is a fictional universe created by Isaac Asimov for other science fiction writers to use as a setting .
`` The Hedgehog and the Fox '' is an essay by philosopher Isaiah Berlin .
Kocharethi ( കൊച്ചരേത്തി ) is a Malayalam novel by Narayan , often described as Kerala 's first tribal novelist , that was published in 1998 .
The Muqaddimah , also known as the Muqaddimah of Ibn Khaldun ( Arabic : مقدّمة ابن خلدون‎ ) or Ibn Khaldun 's Prolegomena ( Ancient Greek : ἡ Προλεγόμενα ) , is a book written by the Ifriqiyan Muslim Arab historian Ibn Khaldun in 1377 which records an early view of universal history .
Le Vin de solitude , published in English as The Wine of Solitude , is a novel by Russian Jewish author Irène Némirovsky ( 1903 -- 1942 ) , who died in the Holocaust .
Italian Hours is a book of travel writing by Henry James published in 1909 .
Hardboiled & Hard Luck ( ハードボイルド／ハードラック Alt : Hādoboirudo . English ) is a novel written by Japanese author Banana Yoshimoto in 1999 and translated into English in 2005 by Michael Emmerich .
Merry Christmas , Mr. Baxter was a novel written and published in 1956 by American author Edward Streeter .
The Present and the Past ( 1953 ) is a novel by Ivy Compton - Burnett about the head of a family who , although outwardly powerful and in charge , is suffering under the fact that he is being belittled and at some point even outright ignored by family and servants alike .
The Antiquarian 's Family , or The Mother - in - law and the Daughter ( La famiglia dell'antiquario , ossia La suocera e la nuora ) is a comedy by Venetian author Carlo Goldoni , first published in 1749 .
William Wetmore Story and His Friends is a biography of sculptor William Wetmore Story by Henry James , published in 1903 .
The Fierce Dispute is a 1929 novel by Helen Hooven Santmyer .
The Terrible Truth About Liberals is a 2001 political , non - fiction book by Neal Boortz .
Desert Encounter ( Danish : Ørkenen Brænder ) is a book written by the Danish journalist Knud Holmboe who had converted to Islam .
`` The Goat and Her Three Kids '' or `` The Goat with Three Kids '' ( Romanian : Capra cu trei iezi ) is an 1875 short story , fable and fairy tale by Romanian author Ion Creangă .
Guenevere , Queen of the Summer Country is a novel by Rosalind Miles , based on Arthurian legend .
They 'd Rather Be Right ( also known as The Forever Machine ) is a science fiction novel by Mark Clifton and Frank Riley .
The Green Brain ( 1966 ) , initially published as Greenslaves , is a science fiction novel by Frank Herbert .
Letters to Family , Friends , and Editors is a book collecting some of Franz Kafka 's letters from 1900 to 1924 .
Worlds in Collision is a book written by Immanuel Velikovsky and first published April 3 , 1950 .
Doctor Fischer of Geneva or The bomb party ( 1980 ) is a novel by the English novelist Graham Greene .
The Road to San Vicente is a book by Leif Borthen about life in the tiny village of Sant Vicent de sa Cala in the far north east of the Spanish island of Ibiza .
Eight Days of Luke is a children 's fantasy novel written by Diana Wynne Jones published in 1975 .
The Starchild Trilogy is a series of three books written by Frederik Pohl and Jack Williamson .
Sessanta racconti ( `` sixty stories '' ) is a 1958 short story collection by the Italian writer Dino Buzzati .

In 1983 , Al Alvarez published , The Biggest Game in Town , a book detailing the 1981 World Series of Poker event .

The Candle in the Wind is the fourth book from the collection The Once and Future King by T. H. White .
On Stranger Tides is a 1987 historical fantasy novel written by Tim Powers .
Rivalry and Tribute is a book written by Bruce Elliot Tapper that offers a peek into a 1970 's village society in India .
The Tale of the Pie and the Patty - Pan ( originally , The Pie and the Patty - Pan ) is a children 's book written and illustrated by Beatrix Potter , and published by Frederick Warne & Co. in October 1905 .

Sophat ( Khmer : រឿងសូផាត ) was the first Khmer romance novel written in 1938 by Rim Kin and was published in 1942 .

Flora Lapponica ( Amsterdam , 1737 ) is an account of the plants of Lapland written by botanist , zoologist and naturalist Carl Linnaeus ( 1707 - 1788 ) following his expedition to Lapland .
On Crimes and Punishments ( Italian : Dei delitti e delle pene ( dei deˈlitti e ddelle ˈpeːne ) ) , is a treatise written by Cesare Beccaria in 1764 .
The Lying Stones of Marrakech ( 2000 ) is the ninth volume of collected essays by the Harvard paleontologist , Stephen Jay Gould .

Tales from the Town of Widows is a lyrical novel written by Colombian - born author James Cañón .
The Enchanted Type - Writer is a collection of short stories by the American author John Kendrick Bangs , written in 1899 in the style that has become known as Bangsian fantasy .

The Invisible Man is a science fiction novella by H. G. Wells .

`` The Remarkable Rocket '' is a short fairytale that was first published in 1888 in The Happy Prince and Other Tales which is a collection of five fairytales written by Oscar Wilde .
`` Esquisse d'un Programme '' is a famous proposal for long - term mathematical research made by the German - born , French mathematician Alexander Grothendieck in 1984 .
Shalimar the Clown is a 2005 novel by Salman Rushdie , the author of The Satanic Verses and Midnight 's Children .

Peacock Ridge ( 66 ° 48′S 51 ° 0′E ) is a ridge standing between Mount Soucek and Mount Porteus , in the north part of the Tula Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Mount Romnaes ( 71 ° 31′S 24 ° 0′E ) is a prominent isolated mountain in Antarctica .
Säntis is among the most prominent summits in the Alps and the most prominent summit in Europe with an observation deck on the top .
Sliven Peak ( Vrah Sliven \'vr&h ' sli - ven\ ) rises to 530 m in the east extremity of Melnik Ridge , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Romeo Island is a rocky island lying off the north coast of Greenwich Island and west of Aitcho Islands in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Johnson Nunataks ( 85 ° 2′S 92 ° 30′W ) are two isolated rock crags , or nunataks , which lie 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) west of Reed Ridge , along the northwest side of Ford Massif in the Thiel Mountains of Antarctica .
Luncke Ridge ( 68 ° 29′S 78 ° 25′E ) is a fairly prominent ridge on the northern side of the eastern extremity of Langnes Fjord in the Vestfold Hills of Antarctica .
Kvithovden Peak ( 72 ° 22′S 0 ° 45′E ) is a peak at the north end of Kvitkjolen Ridge in the Sverdrup Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Rhodes Bluff ( 79 ° 50′S 83 ° 20′W ) is a bare rock bluff 2 nautical miles ( 3.7 km ) northwest of Mount Dolence , forming the northwest end of Enterprise Hills in the Heritage Range of Antarctica .
DeZafra Ridge ( 79 ° 17′S 157 ° 27′E ) is a narrow but prominent rock ridge , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , which extends north from the northeast cliffs of Longhurst Plateau in the Cook Mountains of Antarctica .
Morales Peak ( 86 ° 15′S 126 ° 22′W ) is a peak which rises from the southern part of Metavolcanic Mountain in Antarctica , just east of Reedy Glacier .
The Four Ramps ( 84 ° 42′S 177 ° 35′E ) are a group of four small rock spurs , roughly parallel and projecting through the snow surface , forming the northeast part of Sullivan Ridge on the west side of Ramsey Glacier , Antarctica .
Mount Kazukaitis ( 72 ° 2′S 100 ° 55′W ) is a peak of the Walker Mountains , located at the base of Hughes Peninsula in the western part of Thurston Island , Antarctica .
Exile Nunatak ( 70 ° 19′S 71 ° 16′W ) is an isolated nunatak in the northwest part of Handel Ice Piedmont in the west - central part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Karnobat Pass ( Karnobatski Prohod \kar - no-'bat - ski ' pro - hod\ ) is a 220 m wide and 720 m high pass in Levski Ridge in Tangra Mountains , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
The Fletcher Nunataks ( 74 ° 54′S 72 ° 47′W ) are two nunataks lying 2.2 nautical miles ( 4.1 km ) southwest of Barker Nunatak in the Grossman Nunataks , in Antarctica .
McCarthy Point ( 74 ° 25′S 130 ° 59′W ) is an ice - covered point that marks the northeastern extremity of Grant Island on the seaward edge of the Getz Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
Mount Fedallah ( 65 ° 43′S 62 ° 52′W ) is a mountain approximately 1,250 metres ( 4,100 ft ) high , situated east of the Pip Cliffs , on the north side of Flask Glacier , in the south - east foothills of Madrid Dome in Aristotle Mountains , eastern Graham Land Antarctica .
Manhaul Glacier ( 72 ° 24′S 169 ° 45′E ) is a glacier flowing from the east slopes of Mount Humphrey Lloyd to enter Edisto Inlet just south of Luther Peak , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
McCrilliss Nunatak ( 85 ° 27′S 128 ° 55′W ) is a nunatak marking the north end of the Gierloff Nunataks on the north side of the Wisconsin Range , Horlick Mountains , Antarctica .
Driscoll Island is a narrow , ice - covered island 30 kilometres ( 16 nmi ) long , lying in Block Bay along the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Meander Glacier ( 73 ° 16′S 166 ° 55′E ) is a large meandering tributary to Mariner Glacier in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Krasnov Rocks ( 71 ° 48′S 10 ° 20′E ) are a linear group of rocks 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south - southeast of the summit of Mount Dallmann , in the Orvin Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Hermite Islands ( Spanish : Islas Hermite ) are the islands Hermite , Herschel , Deceit and Hornos as well as the islets Maxwell , Jerdán , Arrecife , Chantieler , Hall , Deceit ( islet ) , and Hasse at almost the southernmost end of South America .
Mount Kropotkin is a peak on the west side of Jøkulkyrkja Mountain in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Sri Lanka ( /sriːˈlɑːŋkə , -ˈlæŋkə/ or i / ʃriː-/ ; Sinhalese - ශ්‍රී ලංකාව , Tamil Ilaṅkai ) , officially the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka and known from the beginning of British colonial rule until 1972 as Ceylon ( /sᵻˈlɒnˌ seɪ-ˌ siː-/ ) , is an island country in South Asia near south - east India .
Perce Point ( 72 ° 8′S 74 ° 38′W ) is a low ice - covered headland 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) west - northwest of Berlioz Point on the southern coast of the Beethoven Peninsula , situated in the wouthwest portion of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Fishtrap Cove ( 68 ° 11′S 67 ° 0′W ) is a small cove 0.1 nautical miles ( 0.2 km ) northwest of Boulder Point on the southwest side of Stonington Island , close off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Gornik Knoll ( Bulgarian : хълм Горник , `` Halm Gornik '' \'h&lm ' gor - nik\ ) is the rocky hill rising to 466 m on the southeast side of Cugnot Ice Piedmont on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
MacKay Peak is an ice - covered pyramidal peak rising to 770 m in Friesland Ridge , Tangra Mountains , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount McIntosh ( 77 ° 31′S 168 ° 41′E ) is a mountain rising to about 2,600 metres ( 8,500 ft ) in the western part of the Kyle Hills , on Ross Island , Antarctica .
Barnard Point is a headland which marks the south - east side of the entrance to False Bay on the south side of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Asparuh Peak ( Asparuhov Vrah \as - pa-'ru - hov ' vr&h\ ) is a peak situated on Livingston Island , Antarctica .
Huey Creek ( 77 ° 36′S 163 ° 7′E ) is a glacial meltwater stream , 1.2 nautical miles ( 2.2 km ) long , flowing south from an ice field west of Mount Falconer to the north - central shore of Lake Fryxell , in Taylor Valley , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Neuburg Peak is a jagged rock peak in Antarctica , 1,840 m , rising 2.5 nautical miles ( 4.6 km ) east of Walker Peak in the southwest part of Dufek Massif , Pensacola Mountains .
Mount Gerlache ( 74 ° 59′S 162 ° 26′E ) is a prominent mountain , 980 metres ( 3,220 ft ) high , standing on the northeast side of Larsen Glacier between Widowmaker Pass and Backstairs Passage Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Vahsel Bay ( German : Vahselbucht ) is a bay about 7 miles wide in the western part of the Luitpold Coast , Antarctica .
Mount Eather ( 70 ° 29′S 65 ° 50′E ) is a mountain about 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south of the Martin Massif in the Porthos Range of the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Metzgar Nunatak ( 74 ° 28′S 72 ° 25′W ) is a nunatak rising to about 1,700 metres ( 5,600 ft ) 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south of Tollefson Nunatak in the Yee Nunataks , Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Anderson Dome is a prominent ice - covered dome mountain rising to 1,475 metres ( 4,840 ft ) on the east side of Gopher Glacier , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) east of the similar - appearing Bonnabeau Dome , in the Jones Mountains in Antarctica .
Erebus Glacier ( 77 ° 40′S 167 ° 6′E ) is a glacier draining the lower southern slopes of Mount Erebus , Ross Island , Antarctica .
Mount Hirman ( 75 ° 28′S 72 ° 46′W ) is a prominent mountain marking the southern end of the Behrendt Mountains , in Ellsworth Land , Antarctica .
Price Bluff ( 86 ° 32′S 144 ° 34′W ) is a large cliff 5 nautical miles ( 9.3 km ; 5.8 mi ) northeast of Mount Mooney , standing near the head of Robison Glacier in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .
Poibrene Heights ( Bulgarian : Поибренски възвишения , `` Poibrenski Vazvisheniya '' \po-'i - bren - ski v&-zvi-'she - ni - ya\ ) are the heights rising to 850 m ( Ravnogor Peak ) on Oscar II Coast , Graham Land in Antarctica .
The Blackwall Mountains ( 68 ° 22′S 66 ° 48′W ) in Antarctica rise to 1,370 metres ( 4,500 ft ) , extending in a west - northwest -- east - southeast direction for 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) and lying close south of Neny Fjord on the west coast of Graham Land .
Moe Point ( 70 ° 19′S 62 ° 23′W ) is a point consisting of a small bare rock bluff , located just south of Croom Glacier on the northwest side of Smith Inlet , in Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Leniz Point , also known as Barbaro Point , is the northern extremity of the small peninsula on which Mount Banck stands , lying 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) south of Bryde Island on the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Mount Hollingshead ( 70 ° 41′S 66 ° 10′E ) is a large peak about 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of Mount Dowie in the Aramis Range of the Prince Charles Mountains in Antarctica .

The Hannam Islands are three small islands lying in the eastern part of Commonwealth Bay , Antarctica , midway between Cape Denison and Cape Gray .
Trigrad Gap ( Trigradska Sedlovina \tri-'grad - ska se - dlo - vi-'na\ ) is a saddle of 500 m height in the Delchev Ridge in the Tangra Mountains of eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .

Alligator Ridge ( 78 ° 27′S 158 ° 48′E ) is a spectacular serrated rock ridge in Antarctica , extending northeast for 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) from Alligator Peak in the Boomerang Range into Skelton Neve .
Vivaldi Glacier ( 70 ° 47′S 69 ° 50′W ) is a glacier lying between the Colbert Mountains and the Lully Foothills , flowing south from Purcell Snowfield into the head of Schubert Inlet on the west coast of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Perrier Bay ( 64 ° 23′S 63 ° 45′W ) is a bay 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) wide indenting the northwest coast of Anvers Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica between Obitel Peninsula and Goten Peninsula .
Paumelle Point ( 65 ° 4′S 64 ° 3′W ) is a point marking the south side of the entrance to Libois Bay and the northwest end of the peninsula that forms the west extremity of Booth Island , in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Gale Escarpment ( 72 ° 55′S 75 ° 23′E ) is a northwest - facing escarpment of rock and ice , standing eastward of Mount Harding and Wilson Ridge in the Grove Mountains of Antarctica .
Jamieson Ridge ( 80 ° 27′S 25 ° 53′W ) is a narrow ridge 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) long , rising to about 1,200 metres ( 4,000 ft ) at the southwestern end of the Herbert Mountains , in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Latady Island is a low ice - covered island off Antarctica , about 60 kilometres ( 35 nmi ) long and more than 20 kilometres ( 10 nmi ) wide , lying 80 kilometres ( 45 nmi ) south of Charcot Island and west of Alexander Island .
Agüero Point is a trapezoid - shaped and mostly ice - covered point projecting 900 m east - northeastwards from the east coast of Ioannes Paulus II Peninsula into Hero Bay , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Mount Moberly ( 64 ° 44′S 63 ° 41′W ) is a steep - sided , snow - covered mountain , 1,535 metres ( 5,040 ft ) high , at the end of the ridge extending southwest from Mount Français in the southern part of Anvers Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Basalt Lake is a small freshwater lake surrounded by three basalt outcrops with `` organ - pipe '' formations in their rocks , situated in the central part of the ice - free Byers Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Kirkpatrick Glacier ( 75 ° 9′S 136 ° 0′W ) is a tributary glacier about 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long , flowing west along the south side of the McDonald Heights to enter the east side of Hull Glacier near the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Ritli Hill ( Bulgarian : хълм Ритли , `` Halm Ritli '' \'h&lm ' rit - li\ ) is a rocky hill rising to 45 m on the south coast of western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Cape Timblón is the conspicuous rocky cape forming the north extremity of Snow Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Collins Glacier ( 73 ° 41′S 65 ° 55′E ) is a glacier about 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) wide at its confluence with the Mellor Glacier , which it feeds from the southwest , located north of Mount Newton in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .

The Dikstra Buttresses ( 69 ° 48′S 69 ° 53′W ) are a group of summits rising to about 1,500 metres ( 5,000 ft ) on the western side of the Douglas Range , northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .

The Full Cupboard of Life is the fifth in The No . 1 Ladies ' Detective Agency series of novels by Alexander McCall Smith , set in Gaborone , Botswana , and featuring the Motswana protagonist Precious Ramotswe .
The Wall of Sound ( also called the Spector Sound ) is a music production formula developed by record producer Phil Spector at Gold Star Studios during the 1960s .
Just what is it that makes today 's homes so different , so appealing ? is a collage by English artist Richard Hamilton .
Humility theology is a school of thought founded by John Templeton .

Peter Guillam is a fictional character in John le Carré 's series of espionage novels .

View of the Domaine Saint - Joseph is a painting by French artist Paul Cézanne .
Dovedale by Moonlight is one of five paintings by Joseph Wright of Derby which uses the picturesque valley of Dovedale as its subject .
Portrait of Wally is a 1912 oil painting by Austrian painter Egon Schiele of Valerie `` Wally '' Neuzil , a woman he met in 1911 when she was 17 years old and who was a model for a number of Schiele 's most striking paintings .
In Front of Yorktown , 1862 - 1863 is an oil painting by Winslow Homer of men from McClellan 's Army of the Potomac , before the Siege of Yorktown .

Portrait of Captain Thomas Coram is a 1740 portrait of philanthropist Thomas Coram painted by William Hogarth .
The Snail ( L'escargot ) is a collage by Henri Matisse .
Astronomer Copernicus , or Conversations with God ( Polish : Astronom Kopernik , czyli rozmowa z Bogiem ) is an oil painting by the Polish artist Jan Matejko , finished in 1873 , depicting Nicolaus Copernicus observing the heavens from a balcony by a tower near the cathedral in Frombork ( seen in the back ) .
It Was My Best Birthday Ever , Charlie Brown is the 38th animated TV special based on characters from the Charles M. Schulz comic strip Peanuts .

The Canova Lions , located in front of the Corcoran Gallery of Art in Washington , D.C. , are copies of a pair of lions sculpted by Antonio Canova in 1792 for the tomb of Pope Clement XIII in St Peter 's in Rome .

Garfield is an American comic strip created by Jim Davis .

Hamburg - Köln - Express GmbH ( HKX ) is a Cologne - based open - access train operating company providing long - distance railway passenger services in Germany .
The Ulbricht Doctrine , named after East German leader Walter Ulbricht , was the assertion that normal diplomatic relations between East Germany and West Germany could occur only if both states fully recognised each other 's sovereignty .
The 9K35 Strela-10 ( Russian : 9К35 `` Стрела-10 '' ; English : arrow ) is a highly mobile , visually aimed , optical / infrared - guided , low - altitude , short - range surface - to - air missile system .
Playfairite is a very rare sulfosalt mineral with chemical formula Pb16Sb18S43 in the monoclinic crystal system , named after the Scottish scientist and mathematician John Playfair .
Riesz spaces are named after Frigyes Riesz who first defined them in his 1928 paper Sur la décomposition des opérations fonctionelles linéaires .
Alatri Cathedral , otherwise the Basilica of Saint Paul ( Italian : Duomo di Alatri ; Basilica concattedrale di San Paolo apostolo ) is the principal church ( duomo ) of Alatri , Lazio , Italy , dedicated to Saint Paul .
Thomsen 's theorem , named after Gerhard Thomsen , is a theorem in elementary geometry .
WBUR - FM ( 90.9 FM ) is a public radio station located in Boston , Massachusetts , owned by Boston University .
Djurleite was named for the Swedish chemist Seved Djurle ( 1928 - -2000 ) , from the University of Uppsala , Sweden , who first synthesized the mineral in 1958 , prior to its discovery in nature .
The Buffett Rule is named after American investor Warren Buffett , who publicly stated in early 2011 that he believed it was wrong that rich people , like himself , could pay less in federal taxes , as a portion of income , than the middle class , and voiced support for increased income taxes on the wealthy .
A Hilbert curve ( also known as a Hilbert space - filling curve ) is a continuous fractal space - filling curve first described by the German mathematician David Hilbert in 1891 , as a variant of the space - filling Peano curves discovered by Giuseppe Peano in 1890 .
Thatcherism describes the conviction politics , economic , social policy , and political style of the British Conservative politician Margaret Thatcher , who was leader of her party from 1975 to 1990 .
The Kaplan Foundation is a foundation dedicated to the scholarship and preservation of the music of Gustav Mahler set up by amateur conductor and businessman Gilbert Kaplan .
In Lie theory and representation theory , the Levi decomposition , conjectured by Killing and Cartan and proved by Eugenio Elia Levi ( 1905 ) , states that any finite - dimensional real Lie algebra g is the semidirect product of a solvable ideal and a semisimple subalgebra .
The Clara database is a database named after Clara Peeters that is operated by the National Museum of Women in the Arts .
Tiffany Blue is the colloquial name for the light medium robin egg blue color associated with Tiffany & Co. , the New York City jewelry company .
Nova Friburgo ( Portuguese pronunciation : ( ˈnɔvɐ fɾiˈbuʁɡu ) , German : Neufreiburg , English : New Fribourg ) is a municipality in the state of Rio de Janeiro in southeastern Brazil .
The Bemaraha woolly lemur ( Avahi cleesei ) , also known as Cleese 's woolly lemur , is a species of woolly lemur native to western Madagascar , named after John Cleese .
In mathematics , an Adams operation , denoted ψk for natural numbers k , is a cohomology operation in topological K - theory , or any allied operation in algebraic K - theory or other types of algebraic construction , defined on a pattern introduced by Frank Adams .
The Thompson shell is the first Unix shell , introduced in the first version of Unix in 1971 , and was written by Ken Thompson .
The band called themselves Rammstein - Flugschau ( Rammstein Airshow ) after the 1988 Ramstein air show disaster .
A Rogowski coil , named after Walter Rogowski , is an electrical device for measuring alternating current ( AC ) or high speed current pulses .
The originally anonymous area became Széll Kálmán tér ( Széll Kálmán Square ) in 1929 , named after the Hungarian prime minister Kálmán Széll .
The Berwick Prize and Senior Berwick Prize are two prizes of the London Mathematical Society awarded in alternating years in memory of William Edward Hodgson Berwick , a previous Vice - President of the LMS .
Dancing Lion is a 2007 Hong Kong comedy film directed by and starring Francis Ng .
Katarina Barley ( * 19 . November 1968 in Cologne ) is a German lawyer , politician and member of the 18th German Bundestag .
Cees Nooteboom ( Dutch pronunciation : ( seːs noːtəboːm ) ; born 31 July 1933 ) is a Dutch novelist , poet , and journalist .
Henry Gréville ( 12 October 1842 in Paris -- 1902 ) , pen name for Mrs. Alice Durand , born Fleury , was a French writer .
Otto Bernhardt ( born 13 February 1942 in Rendsburg ) is a German politician of the CDU .
Paul Éluard ( French pronunciation : ​(elɥar ) ) , born Eugène Émile Paul Grindel ( ( ɡʁɛ̃dɛl ) ; 14 December 1895 -- 18 November 1952 ) , was a French poet and one of the founders of the surrealist movement .
André Damien ( born 10 July 1930 at Paris ) is an eminent lawyer and politician , who was formerly head of the French Bar Association .
Bernard Carayon ( born 1 October 1957 ) was a member of the French parliament .
Mathurin Régnier ( December 21 , 1573 -- October 22 , 1613 ) was a French satirist .
Jacques Chaban - Delmas (; 7 March 1915 -- 10 November 2000 ) was a French Gaullist politician .
Pierre Corneille (; 6 June 1606 -- 1 October 1684 ) was a French tragedian .
Yvon Delbos ( 7 May 1885 -- 15 November 1956 ) was a French Radical - Socialist Party politician and minister .
Jacques Élie Henri Ambroise Ner ( 7 December 1861 -- February 6 , 1938 ) , also known by the pseudonym Han Ryner , was a French individualist anarchist philosopher and activist and a novelist .
Abbé François Blanchet ( 26 January 1707 -- 29 January 1784 ) was a French littérateur , or Intellectual .
Jacques Marie Boutet ( 25 March 1745 -- 13 February 1812 ) was a French actor and comic dramatist from Lunéville .
Paracelsus ( /ˌpærəˈsɛlsəs/ ; late 1493 -- September 24 , 1541 ) , born Philippus Aureolus Theophrastus Bombastus von Hohenheim , was a Swiss German philosopher , physician , botanist , astrologer , and general occultist .
Robert Lehr ( 20 August 1883 in Celle -- 13 October 1956 in Düsseldorf ) was a German politician ( DNVP , CDU ) .
Paul Andréota ( born 11 December 1917 in La Rochelle , France - died 14 November 2007 in La Rochelle , France ) was a French novelist and screenwriter .
Edurne García Almagro ( Spanish pronunciation : ( eˈðurne ) ; born 22 December 1985 ) , known professionally as Edurne , is a Spanish singer , actress , and TV presenter .
François - Jean - Hyacinthe Feutrier ( 3 April 1785 -- 27 June 1830 ) was a French Catholic priest who became Bishop of Beauvais .
Rambhadracharya can speak 22 languages and is a spontaneous poet and writer in Sanskrit , Hindi , Awadhi , Maithili , and several other languages .
Violette Leduc ( 7 April 1907 -- 28 May 1972 ) was a French author .
Pierre Minet ( Reims 1909 - - Paris 1975 ) was a French poet and writer , whose early career is closely associated to the `` Grand Jeu '' movement and to his devotion to Roger Gilbert - Lecomte .
Alain Richard , born on 29 August 1945 , in Paris , is a French politician .
Adrienne Lecouvreur ( 5 April 1692 -- 20 March 1730 ) was a French actress , considered by many as the greatest of her time .
Jacques Attali ( French : ( ʒak atali ) ; born 1 November 1943 ) is a French economist , writer and senior civil servant .
Henri Pourrat ( 7 May 1887 in Ambert ( Puy de Dome ) -- 16 July 1959 in Ambert ) was a French writer and anthropologist who collected the oral literature of the Auvergne .

Mary Elizabeth Hawker ( 1848 - -1908 ) was an English writer of novellas and short stories .
Jean François Sarrazin ( ca . 1611 -- 5 December 1654 ) , or Sarasin , was a French writer .
Pierre Reverdy ( French : ( ʁəvɛʁdi ) ; September 13 , 1889 -- June 17 , 1960 ) was a French poet whose works were inspired by and subsequently proceeded to influence the provocative art movements of the day , Surrealism , Dadaism and Cubism .
Claude Le Coz ( 1740 - -1815 ) was a French Catholic bishop .
Annie Fratellini ( 14 November 1932 - -30 June 1997 ) was a French circus artist , clown , singer and film actress .
Jacques Garnier , also called Garnier de Saintes , was born in Saintes on 30 March 1755 , and drowned in the Ohio river in 1817 or 1818 was a French politician , a lawyer and a revolutionary .

Elsa Zylberstein ( born 16 October 1968 ) is a French film , TV , and stage actress .
Martijn Theodoor Houtsma ( Irnsum , Friesland , 15 January 1851 -- Utrecht , 9 February 1943 ) , often referred to as M. Th . Houtsma , was a Dutch orientalist .
René de Obaldia ( born October 22 , 1918 in Hong Kong ) is a French playwright and poet .
Alphonse Arzel ( 20 September 1927 -- 21 February 2014 in Ploudalmézeau , Finistère ) was a French politician , a member of the French Senate representing the department of Finistère , mayor of Ploudalmézeau , and president of the Association of the mayors of Finistère ( AMF 29 ) .
Peter Kassovitz ( born 17 November 1938 ) is a French film director and scriptwriter .
Alain Lambert ( born in Alençon , on 20 July 1946 ) is a French politician and a notary by profession .
Richard Canal ( born August 16 , 1953 ) is a French science fiction writer who has won the Prix Rosny - Aîné twice .
Bertrand Tavernier ( born 25 April 1941 ) is a French director , screenwriter , actor and producer .

Simon Heere Heeresma ( 9 March 1932 -- 26 June 2011 ) was a Dutch author and poet .
René Dosière is best known for his many questions to the government regarding the expenses of the services of the French presidency .

Michèle Bernstein ( born 28 April 1932 ) is a French novelist and critic , most usually remembered as a member of the Situationist International from its foundation in 1957 until 1967 , and as the first wife of its most prominent member , Guy Debord .
Miroslav Táborský ( born 9 November 1959 in Prague , Czechoslovakia ) is a Czech actor who has appeared on Czech television series , as well as in American movies .
Charles - Marie de Féletz ( 3 January 1767 , Gumont -- 11 February 1850 ) was a French churchman , journalist and literary critic .
Alain Daniélou ( 4 October 1907 -- 27 January 1994 ) was a French historian , intellectual , musicologist , Indologist , and a noted Western convert to and expert on Shaivite Hinduism .

Alina Reyes ( born Aline Patricia Nardone on 9 February 1956 ) is a French writer , best known for her literary treatment of eroticism .

Edmond Brazès ( Céret ( Pyrénées - Orientales ) , 1893 -- 10 June 1980 ) was a French writer in both Catalan and French .

Suzanne Curchod ( 1737 -- 6 May 1794 ) was a French - Swiss salonist and writer .
Gerrit Paape Delft ( Delft , 4 February 1752 -- The Hague , 7 December 1803 ) was a Dutch plateelschilder ( painter of earthenware and stoneware ) , poet , journalist , novelist , judge , columnist and ( at the end of his career ) ministerial civil servant .
Henri Evrard , marquis de Dreux - Brézé ( 1762 - 1829 ) was a member of the French nobility who at the age of twenty - seven played a role in the meeting of the states - general in 1789 .
Kim Jong - il ( Korean pronunciation : ( ɡ̊imd͜zɔŋil ) ; 16 February 1941/1942 -- 17 December 2011 ) was the supreme leader of the Democratic People 's Republic of Korea ( DPRK ) , commonly referred to as North Korea , from 1994 to 2011 .
Gérard Chaliand ( born 1934 ) is a French expert in geopolitics who has published widely on irregular warfare and military strategy .
Gabriel Nuchelmans ( 15 May 1922 Oud Gastel -- 6 August 1996 , Wassenaar ) was a Dutch philosopher , focusing on the history of philosophy , especially philosophy of the Middle Ages , as well as logic and philosophy of language .

Francis Marmande ( born 1945 ) is a French author , musician and journalist for the French newspaper Le Monde since 1977 .
Abel Jacquin ( 1893 - -1968 ) was a French actor who appeared in more than thirty films between 1930 and 1956 .

The Alabama map turtle ( Graptemys pulchra ) is a species of emydid turtle endemic to the southern United States .
Tytthodiplatys is an extinct genus of earwig in the family Diplatyidae known from a Cretaceous fossil found in Myanmar .
Monamphiura is a genus of brittle star echinoderms of the family Amphiuridae .
Holynskirbus lesnei is a species of beetle in the family Buprestidae , the only species in the genus Holynskirbus .
The Taiwan angelshark ( Squatina formosa ) is an angel shark of the family Squatinidae found around Taiwan between latitudes 24 ° N and 22 ° N , at depths of between 185 and 220 m. Its length is up to 46 cm for an immature female - there are no adult specimens .
The Lake Upemba forest tree frog , Leptopelis parbocagii , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Angola , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Malawi , Mozambique , Tanzania , and Zambia .
The Tennessee warbler ( Oreothlypis peregrina ) is a New World warbler that breeds in eastern North America and winters in southern Central America and northern South America .
Pupatonia is a genus of minute sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Eatoniellidae , the eatoniellids .
The Pattipola caecilian , Ichthyophis orthoplicatus , is a species of caecilian endemic to Sri Lanka .
The Iberian rock lizard ( Iberolacerta monticola or Lacerta monticola ) is a species of lizard in the Lacertidae family .
The Kordofan sparrow , also known as the Kordofan rufous sparrow , ( Passer cordofanicus ) is a sparrow found only in northwestern Sudan and eastern Chad .
Aquilaria is a genus of fifteen species of trees in the Thymelaeaceae , native to southeast Asia .
The Lord Howe parakeet ( Cyanoramphus subflavescens ) , also known as the Lord Howe red - fronted parakeet , is an extinct parrot endemic to Lord Howe Island in the Tasman Sea , part of New South Wales , Australia .
The Italian bleak or white bleak ( Alburnus albidus ) is a species of freshwater fish in the Cyprinidae family , endemic to Italy .
Pteromalinae is a parasitoid wasp subfamily in the family Pteromalidae .
Tohoraata is a member of the family Eomysticetidae , a family of primitive baleen - bearing mysticetes ( chaeomysticetes ) .
The Baja California collared lizard ( Crotaphytus vestigium ) is a large - bodied species of lizard with a broad head , short snout , granular scales , and two distinct black collar markings .
Adromischus is a genus of easily propagated leaf succulents from the Crassulaceae family .
Rhodocyphella is a genus of cyphelloid fungi in the Tricholomataceae family .
The Death Valley pupfish ( Cyprinodon salinus ) , also known as Salt Creek pupfish , is found in Death Valley National Park .
Emiliodonta is an extinct genus of bivalve in the extinct family Praenuculidae .
Catonyx is an extinct genus of ground sloth of the family Mylodontidae , endemic to South America during the Late Pleistocene epochs .
Arethuseae is a mid - sized tribe of orchids in the subfamily Epidendroideae .
The Etmopteridae are a family of sharks in the order Squaliformes , commonly known as lantern sharks .
The Niau kingfisher ( Todiramphus gertrudae ) is a species of bird in the family Alcedinidae .
Shortridge 's rat ( Thallomys shortridgei ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Euaptetoceras is an evolute hammatoceratid ammonite from the lower Middle Jurassic , included in the family Hammatoceratidae and the subfamility Hammatoceratinae .
Cybocephalus is a genus of beetles in the family Cybocephalidae , previously belonging to the subfamily Cybocephalinae of the family Nitidulidae .
The Galápagos fur seal ( Arctocephalus galapagoensis ) breeds on the Galápagos Islands in the eastern Pacific , west of mainland Ecuador .
Idiocolpodes tsaratanensis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Idiocolpodes .
Pseudotrechus mutilatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pseudotrechus .
Zuluscaphites is an extinct genus of cephalopod belonging to the Ammonite subclass from France during the Cretaceous .
The Baja California rock squirrel ( Otospermophilus atricapillus ) is a species of rodent in the family Sciuridae .
The authors of the paper describing Darwinius classified it as a member of the primate family Notharctidae , subfamily Cercamoniinae , suggesting that it has the status of a significant transitional form ( a `` link '' ) between the prosimian and simian ( `` anthropoid '' ) primate lineages .
Anita 's leaf - eared mouse ( Phyllotis anitae ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Machairasaurus was in 2010 assigned to the Oviraptoridae , more precisely to the Ingeniinae .
The Angolan vlei rat ( Otomys anchietae ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Pyrotheriidae is the only family in the order Pyrotheria , provided one does not include the Paleocene genus , Carodnia .
Geukensia is a genus of marine bivalve mollusc in the Mytilidae family , naturally found in the western Atlantic .
Amelus nigripennis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Amelus .
The Daurian starling ( Agropsar sturninus ) , also known as the purple - backed starling , is a species of starling in the family Sturnidae , and is sometimes included in the genus Sturnus or Sturnia .
Onithochiton is a genus of chitons in the family Chitonidae , which is distributed from Australia and New Zealand to South Africa .
Nitor is a genus of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Helicarionidae .
The Lima leaf - eared mouse ( Phyllotis limatus ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Speke 's weaver ( Ploceus spekei ) is a familiar East African songbird .
The Texas brown snake ( Storeria dekayi texana ) , a subspecies of Storeria dekayi , is a nonvenomous snake in the family Colubridae .
The Notothyladaceae is the only family of hornworts in the order Notothyladales .
The Abdim 's stork , ( Ciconia abdimii ) also known as white - bellied stork , is a black stork with grey legs , red knees and feet , grey bill and white underparts .
Ohioceras is an extinct suborthochonic nautiloid from the Silurian of Ohio belonging to the orthoceroid family Kionoceratidae .
Thersiteidae is an extinct family of fossil sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the superfamily Stromboidea , the true conchs and their allies .
Metachanda is the sole genus in the small family Metachandidae of moths .
The Diamond Y springsnail , scientific name Tryonia adamantina , is a species of small freshwater snail with a gill and an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Dalechampia is a genus of plant of the family Euphorbiaceae and of the monogeneric subtribe Dalechampiinae .
Jahn 's tree frog , Hyloscirtus jahni , is a species of frog in the Hylidae family endemic to Venezuela .
Tschudi 's yellow - shouldered bat ( Sturnira oporaphilum ) , is an extant species of leaf - nosed bat indigenous to Argentina , Ecuador , and Peru , with its range also encompassing Bolivia .
Rossbeevera is a genus of sequestrate ( truffle - like ) fungi in the family Boletaceae .
Parallelura was a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it is now considered a synonym of Macaldenia .
Terfezia is a genus of truffle - like fungi within the Pezizaceae family .
Micrairoideae is a subfamily of the grass family Poaceae , distributed in tropical and subtropical regions .
Udranomia is a Neotropical genus in the family Hesperiidae ( Eudaminae ) .
Eliea ( or Eliaea Cambess . , an orthographic variant ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Hypericaceae .
Martiana clausa is a species of crab in the family Pseudothelphusidae , the only species in the genus Martiana .
Leptidea is a genus of butterflies of family Pieridae , the whites and yellows .
Luambwa barb ( Barbus cercops ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Barbus .
The Pocilloporidae are a family of stony corals in the order Scleractinia occurring in the Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Euclia is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
The Kavirondo barb ( Barbus sexradiatus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
Yigoga is a genus of moths of the Noctuidae family , it was placed as a synonym of Dichagyris by Lafontain & Fibiger in 2003 .
Koelliker 's glass lizard ( Hyalosaurus koellikeri ) , also called commonly the Moroccan glass lizard , is a species of lizard in the family Anguidae .
Donaldson Smith 's nightjar ( Caprimulgus donaldsoni ) is a species of nightjar in the Caprimulgidae family .
