Marlierea is a genus of flowering plants in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1833 .
The Angoni vlei rat ( Otomys angoniensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Helcogramma steinitzi , known commonly as the Red triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Helcogramma .
The Huon melidectes or Huon honeyeater ( Melidectes foersteri ) is a species of bird in the Meliphagidae family .
Sloanoglymmius planatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Sloanoglymmius .
The Andaman bulbul ( Pycnonotus fuscoflavescens ) is a member of the bulbul family of passerine birds .
Notoacmea is a southern genus of true limpets , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Lottiidae , the true limpets .
Sageretia ( mock buckthorn or sageretia ) is a genus of about 35 species of shrubs and small trees in the family Rhamnaceae , native to southern and eastern Asia and northeast Africa .
Goniurellia is a genus of the family Tephritidae , better known as fruit flies .
Calochlaena is a genus of ferns within the Dicksoniaceae family .
The Atlantic goliath grouper or itajara ( Epinephelus itajara ) is a large saltwater fish of the grouper family found primarily in shallow tropical waters among coral and artificial reefs at depths from 5 to 50 m ( 16 to 164 ft ) .
Seipp 's day gecko ( Phelsuma seippi Meier , 1987 ) is a diurnal species of geckos .
Barclaya is a genus of 3 - 4 species of flowering plants usually included in the family Nymphaeaceae but sometimes given their own family status as Barclayaceae on the basis of an extended perianth tube ( combined sepals and petals ) arising from the top of the ovary and by stamens that are joined basally .
Ginema is a genus of ground beetles ( family Carabidae ) .
Centrolobium is a genus of legume in the Fabaceae family , and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Pterocarpus clade of the Dalbergieae .
The Archduke , Lexias dirtea , is a species of butterfly of the family Nymphalidae .
It is the largest subfamily of Megachilidae Subfamily Megachilinae Tribe Lithurgini Lithurgus Microthurge Trichothurgus Tribe Osmiini Afroheriades Ashmeadiella Atoposmia Bekilia Chelostoma Haetosmia Heriades have narrow abdominal bands .
Blasius 's horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus blasii ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae found throughout large parts of the Mediterranean , Middle East and Northern Africa .
Batasio is a genus of catfish of the family Bagridae .
The Indian day gecko , Cnemaspis indica , is a species of gecko found in India ( Nilgiri Hills / Travancore ) .
Appertiella is a genus of an aquatic plant of the family Hydrocharitaceae described as a genus in 1982 .
Caesalpinioideae is a botanical name at the rank of subfamily , placed in the large family Fabaceae or Leguminosae .
Wurmbea is a genus of perennial herbs in the family Colchicaceae , native to Africa and Australia .
Minuphloeus mixtus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Minuphloeus .
Sedoreovirinae ( sedo = smooth ) is a subfamily of the Reoviridae family of viruses .
Parajubaea is a genus of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family , and coconut palm trees .
Aluterus heudelotii Hollard , 1855 ( Dotterel filefish ) Aluterus monoceros Linnaeus , 1758 ( Unicorn leatherjacket filefish ) Aluterus schoepfii Walbaum , 1792 ( Orange filefish ) Aluterus scriptus Osbeck , 1765 ( Scribbled leatherjacket filefish )
The Transvaal girdled lizard , Cordylus vittifer , is a very flattened girdled lizard from northeastern South Africa , Swaziland , and southeastern Botswana .
The Tonnoidea are a superfamily of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the clade Littorinimorpha .
Megabats constitute the suborder Megachiroptera , and its only family Pteropodidae of the order Chiroptera ( bats ) .
Caffromorda platycephala is a species of beetle in the family Mordellidae , the only species in the genus Caffromorda .
Anodontoides is a genus of freshwater mussel , an aquatic bivalve mollusk in the family Unionidae , the river mussels .
Conostylis is a genus of perennial herbs in the family Haemodoraceae commonly known as ' cone flowers , endemic to the south west of Western Australia .
The Paraguaian hairy dwarf porcupine , Sphiggurus spinosus , is a South American porcupine species from the family Erethizontidae .
Hespererato is a genus of small sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Triviidae , the false cowries or trivias .
The Bengal fox ( Vulpes bengalensis ) , also known as the Indian fox , is a fox endemic to the Indian subcontinent and is found from the Himalayan foothills and Terai of Nepal through southern India and from southern and eastern Pakistan to eastern India and southeastern Bangladesh .
Elminia is a genus of bird in the flycatcher family Stenostiridae .
Kasner 's dwarf burrowing skink or Kasner 's burrowing skink ( Scelotes kasneri ) is a species of skink in the Scincidae family .
Kuraishia is a genus of two species of ascomycetous yeasts in the family Saccharomycetaceae .
Acosmerycoides is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species Acosmerycoides harterti , which is found from Assam in India , eastwards across southern China to Taiwan and south to Thailand , Laos and Vietnam .
The New England tree frog or glandular tree frog ( Litoria subglandulosa ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae , endemic to Australia .
The Midas free - tailed bat ( Mops midas ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae .
Pterymarchia is a genus of large predatory sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Muricidae , the rock snails or murex snails .
The Ningaloo maskray ( Neotrygon ningalooensis ) is a species of stingray in the family Dasyatidae , found along the northwestern coast of Australia .
The Fiji white - eye ( Zosterops explorator ) is a species of passerine bird in the white - eye family Zosteropidae .
Xenophrys parallela or Megophrys parallelus is a species of frog in the Megophryidae family .
Hellwald 's spiny rat ( Maxomys hellwaldii ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Nystia is an extinct genus of fossil freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod molluscs in the family Truncatellidae .
The Zayante band - winged grasshopper ( Trimerotropis infantilis ) is a species of insect in the family Acrididae .
Amanitoideae is a subfamily of the fungi or mushroom family Amanitaceae .
Florissantoraphidia funerata is an extinct species of snakefly , originally assigned to the raphidiid genus Raphidia , but subsequently transferred to the genus Florissantoraphidia .
The Bornean horseshoe bat ( Rhinolophus borneensis ) is a species of bat in the family Rhinolophidae .
Burchell 's sandgrouse ( Pterocles burchelli ) is a species of bird in the Pteroclididae family .
Pseudotrechisibus sphaericus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Pseudotrechisibus .
The Cuban tody ( Todus multicolor ) is a bird species in the family Todidae that is restricted to Cuba and adjacent islands .
Walcottoceras is a cephalopod genus from the Lower Ordovician included in the ellesmerocerid family Protocycloceratidae according Rousseau Flower in 1964 .
Caeciliusetae is an infraorder of Psocoptera , in the suborder Psocomorpha .
Discourella is a genus of mites in the order Mesostigmata , placed in its own family , Discourellidae .
Rondeletia bicolor is a species of redmouth whalefish known only from the eastern Atlantic Ocean , where it is found at depths of around 3,003 m ( 9,852 ft ) .
The Malabar trevally , Carangoides malabaricus , ( also known as the Malabar jack , Malabar kingfish and nakedshield kingfish ) is a species of large inshore marine fish of the jack family , Carangidae .
Neoscona is a genus of spider in the family Araneidae ( araneids ) with a mostly pantropical distribution .
The Hunter 's cisticola ( Cisticola hunteri ) is a species of bird in the Cisticolidae family .
The Christmas wrasse , Thalassoma trilobatum , is a species of wrasse native to the Indian Ocean and the western Pacific Ocean .
The Megalyroidea are a small hymenopteran superfamily that includes a single family , Megalyridae , with eight genera ( plus three extinct ones ) and at least 45 extant species .
Hiekesia africana is a species of beetle in the family Monotomidae , the only species in the genus Hiekesia .
The genus Tanatchivia is a genus of insect in the family Asilidae .
Diapheridae is a family of air - breathing land snails , terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the superfamily Streptaxoidea .
The Pertyoideae are a subfamily of the Asteraceae , or sunflower family , of the flowering plants .
The Palau nightjar ( Caprimulgus phalaena ) is a species of nightjar endemic to Palau .
Cinnamodendron is a genus of plants in family Canellaceae described as a genus in 1840 .
Palatigum trichostoma is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Palatigum .
The most recent cladistic analysis of ankylosaur phylogeny does not include Animantarx , although the authors recognize the genus as Nodosauridae incertae sedis because of its rounded supraorbital protrusions and a `` knoblike '' acromion on the scapula .
Allendia chilensis is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Allendia .
Adriatic blenny , Microlipophrys adriaticus , is a species of combtooth blenny widespread in the Mediterranean Sea , the Adriatic Sea and the Aegean Sea , also known from the Sea of Marmara and the Black Sea .
The Peruvian thick - knee ( Burhinus superciliaris ) is a species of bird in the family Burhinidae .
Poecilotheria is a genus of the spiders family Theraphosidae currently containing 15 species of arboreal tarantula .
The Alashan ground squirrel ( Spermophilus alashanicus ) is a species of squirrel .
Rastrelliger is a mackerel genus in the family Scombridae .
Anthia is a genus of the ground beetle family , the Carabidae .
Alfaroa is a genus of evergreen trees in the Juglandaceae family of the Fagales , growing in montaine and submontaine tropical rain forests in Central America .
Heliofungia is a genus of stony corals in the family Fungiidae .
Ammopelmatus is a genus of insect in the family Stenopelmatidae .
Peleteria is a widespread genus of flies in the family Tachinidae .
Gagrellina vestita is a species of harvestmen in a monotypic genus in the family Sclerosomatidae .
Pleurocolpus boileaui is a species of crabs in the family Xanthidae , the only species in the genus Pleurocolpus .
The Algerian mouse , or western Mediterranean mouse , ( Mus spretus ) is a wild species of mouse closely related to the house mouse , native to open habitats around the western Mediterranean .
Gyps is a genus of Old World vultures in the bird family Accipitridae .
Campichthys galei ( Duncker , 1909 ) ( Gale 's pipefish ) Campichthys nanus C. E. Dawson , 1977 Campichthys tricarinatus C. E. Dawson , 1977 ( Three - keel pipefish ) Campichthys tryoni ( J. D. Ogilby , 1890 ) ( Tryon 's pipefish )
The Caucasian toad ( Bufo verrucosissimus ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae .
Equatorial spitting cobra ( Naja sumatrana ) also called the black spitting cobra , Malayan spitting cobra , golden spitting cobra , or Sumatran spitting cobra , is a species of spitting cobra found in Southeast Asia .
The Hemprich 's hornbill ( Tockus hemprichii ) is a species of hornbill in the Bucerotidae family .
Whitehead 's spiny rat ( Maxomys whiteheadi ) is a species of rodent in the family Muridae .
Siau Island tarsier ( Tarsius tumpara ) is a species of tarsier from the tiny volcanic island of Siau .
The Santa Cruz white - eye ( Zosterops sanctaecrucis ) is a species of bird in the Zosteropidae family .
Rolán & Rubio ( 2002 : 46 ) hold Discopsis as a valid genus , distinct from Cochliolepis Stimpson , 1858 , on the grounds that the latter belongs in the family Vitrinellidae and the former in Tornidae .
The Accipitridae , one of the four families within the order Accipitriformes ( the other order of diurnal birds of prey being Falconiformes ) , are a family of small to large birds with strongly hooked bills and variable morphology based on diet .
Suessenguthia is a genus of the Acanthaceae plant family comprising six species of shrubs with showy , tubular flowers arranged in few - flowered heads .
The Thripinae belong to the common thrips family Thripidae and include around 1,400 species in 150 genera .
The Malawi spinyeel ( Mastacembelus shiranus ) is a species of fish in the Mastacembelidae family .
The Peltoceratinae comprise a subfamily in the Aspidoceratidae , ( middle and upper Jurassic perisphinctacean ammonites ) .
Choerades is a genus of robber flies described by Walker in 1851 , belonging to the family Asilidae , subfamily Laphriinae .
Xylariopsis is a genus of beetles in the family Cerambycidae , containing the following species : subgenus Falsosybra Xylariopsis fulvonotata ( Pic , 1928 ) subgenus Xylariopsis Xylariopsis esakii Mitono , 1943 Xylariopsis iriei Hayashi , 1976 Xylariopsis mimica Bates , 1884
The Carajás woodcreeper ( Xiphocolaptes carajaensis ) is a species of bird in the Dendrocolaptinae subfamily , the woodcreepers .
Nepenthes ( /nᵻˈpɛnθiːz/ ) , also known as tropical pitcher plants , is a genus of carnivorous plants in the monotypic family Nepenthaceae .
The American sailfin eel ( Letharchus velifer , also known as the Sailfin eel ) is an eel in the family Ophichthidae ( worm / snake eels ) .
Andronymus is an Afrotropical genus of Grass Skippers in the family Hesperiidae .
The Mexican shrew ( Megasorex gigas ) is a species of mammal from the subfamily Soricinae in the family Soricidae .
The Huallaga tanager or black - bellied tanager ( Ramphocelus melanogaster ) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae .
The Madagascan swamp warbler ( Acrocephalus newtoni ) is a species of Old World warbler in the Acrocephalidae family .
Eudeilinia is a genus of moths belonging to the subfamily Drepaninae .
Palaina is a genus of minute land snails with opercula , terrestrial gastropod mollusks or micromollusks in the family Diplommatinidae .
The Lafresnaye 's piculet ( Picumnus lafresnayi ) is a species of bird in the Picidae family .
The Tonga ground skink ( Tachygyia microlepis ) is an extinct species of skink in the Scincidae family .
Stenocercus is a genus of South American lizards , commonly called whorltail iguanas , of the Tropiduridae family .
The Hernandiaceae are a family of flowering plants , angiosperms , in order Laurales .
Siphonops ( ringed caecilians ) is a genus of amphibian in the Siphonopidae family .
Abichites is Ceratitid genus , assigned to the family Dzhulfitidae .
Prosthiostomidae is a family of free - living marine turbellarian flatworms in the sub order Cotylea .
Abyarachryson signaticolle is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Abyarachryson .
Delalande 's sand frog ( Tomopterna delalandii ) is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family endemic to South Africa .
Dictyanthus is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1844 .
Barticaria caeruleus is a species of beetle in the family Megalopodidae , the only species in the genus Barticaria .
The Y - patterned moray eel ( Gymnothorax berndti ) is a deep - water moray eel found in coral reefs in the Pacific and western Indian Oceans at depths to 300 m. It was first named by Snyder in 1904 , and is also commonly known as Berndt 's moray eel .
The Arabian accentor or Yemen accentor ( Prunella fagani ) is a species of bird in the Prunellidae family .
Lunaria ( common name honesty ) is a genus of flowering plants in the family Brassicaceae , native to central and southern Europe .
The Japanese tree frog ( Hyla japonica ) is a species of tree frog distributed from Hokkaidō to Yakushima in Japan and from Korea along the Ussuri River to northeastern China , northern Mongolia , and the southern Russian Far East .
Ampelocissus ( suan lian teng shu in Chinese ) is a genus of Vitaceae having 90 or more species found variously in tropical Africa , Asia , Central America , and Oceania .
Machairodontini is an extinct tribe of large saber - toothed cats of the subfamily Machairodontinae , that lived in Europe , Asia , Africa , and North America , during the late middle Miocene through late Pleistocene living from 11.6 mya--11 000 years ago .
Cancellariidae , common name the nutmeg snails or nutmeg shells , are a family of small to medium - large sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Neogastropoda .
The Natal dwarf puddle frog ( Phrynobatrachus natalensis ) is a species of frog in the Phrynobatrachidae family .
Pseudois is a genus in the subfamily Caprinae comprising two species , the bharal ( Pseudois nayaur ) and the dwarf blue sheep ( Pseudois schaeferi ) .
Lobithelphusa mexicana is a species of crab in the family Pseudothelphusidae , the only species in the genus Lobithelphusa .
The Calayan rail ( Gallirallus calayanensis ) is a flightless bird of the rail , moorhen , and coot family ( Rallidae ) that inhabits Calayan Island in the Philippines .
Parastizocera procera is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parastizocera .
Bruno 's casque - headed frog ( Aparasphenodon brunoi ) is a species of frog in the family Hylidae .
Senecio cadiscus is a species of aquatic flowering plant in the aster family , Asteraceae .
Stenochilus is a genus under the Stenochilidae family .
The Cyprus warbler ( Sylvia melanothorax ) is a typical warbler which breeds on Cyprus .
The Hemerobiiformia are a suborder of lacewing insects in the order Neuroptera .
The Timor blue flycatcher ( Cyornis hyacinthinus ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Norfolkia brachylepis , known commonly as the Tropical scaly - headed triplefin , is a species of triplefin blenny in the genus Norfolkia .
The Hodgson 's frogmouth ( Batrachostomus hodgsoni ) is a species of bird in the Podargidae family .

In taxonomy , Pseudomuriella is a genus of green algae , specifically of the class Chlorophyceae .
Dactylobatus armatus or the Skilletskate , is a small - bodied , deepwater skate .
The American three - toed woodpecker ( Picoides dorsalis ) is a medium - sized woodpecker ( family Picidae ) .
The Alfred 's blind skink ( Dibamus alfredi ) is a blind species of lizard in the genus Dibamus .

The Laysan hedyleptan moth ( Omiodes laysanensis ) is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .

The Curlfin sole , Pleuronichthys decurrens , is a flatfish of the family Pleuronectidae .
Christy 's tree frog , Leptopelis christyi , is a species of frog in the Arthroleptidae family found in Cameroon , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Gabon , Tanzania , and Uganda , and possibly Burundi , the Central African Republic , the Republic of the Congo , Kenya , Rwanda , and the Sudan .
Oncomelania is a genus of very small tropical freshwater snails , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Pomatiopsidae .
The Keast 's tube - nosed fruit bat ( Nyctimene keasti ) is a species of megabat in the family Pteropodidae found in Babar , Tanimbar , and the Kai Islands .
Halecium is a genus of hydrozoa in the Haleciidae family , consisting of approximately 120 species .
Kalinowski 's mastiff bat ( Mormopterus kalinowskii ) is a species of bat in the family Molossidae , the free - tailed bats .
The Mexican tetra or blind cave fish ( Astyanax mexicanus ) is a freshwater fish of the family Characidae of the order Characiformes .

Cinetodus is a genus of sea catfishes ( order Siluriformes ) of the family Ariidae .

Micromys is a genus of small rodents in the subfamily Murinae .
Ochsenheimeria is a genus of moth of the Ypsolophidae family and only genus in the Ochsenheimeriinae subfamily .
Ascetostoma is a genus of mostly small deep water sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Chilodontidae .
Cyrtopodion is a large genus in the family Gekkonidae ( geckos ) .
Geocaulon is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the family Santalaceae containing the single species Geocaulon lividum , which is known by the common names northern comandra and false toadflax .

Leach 's anole ( Anolis leachii ) is a species of anole lizard that is native to Antigua and Barbuda , an island - nation in the Caribbean Lesser Antilles , where it can be found on both main islands .
Squid are members of the class Cephalopoda , subclass Coleoidea , order Teuthida , which has two major suborders , Myopsina and Oegopsina ( including giant squid such as Architeuthis dux ) .

The Phasianinae ( Horsfield , 1821 ) are a subfamily of the pheasant family ( Phasianidae ) of landfowl , the order Galliformes .
Coloraderpeton is an extinct genus of aïstopod lepospondyl within the family Oestocephalidae .
Consolida is a genus of about 40 species of annual flowering plants in the family Ranunculaceae , native to western Europe , the Mediterranean and Asia .

Flavocetraria is a genus of lichenized fungi within the Parmeliaceae family .

Fusicolla is a genus of seven species of ascomycete fungi in the family Nectriaceae .
Mammuthus lamarmorai is a species of mammoth which lived during the late Middle and Upper Pleistocene ( between 450,000 to perhaps 40,000 years ) on the island of Sardinia .
The family Talpidae includes the moles , shrew moles , desmans , and other intermediate forms of small insectivorous mammals of the order Soricomorpha .
Dimerocostus is a group of plants in the Costaceae described as a genus in 1891 .
The Australian swiftlet ( Aerodramus terraereginae ) is a small bird belonging to the genus Aerodramus in the swift family , Apodidae .

Prothoe is a genus of charaxine butterflies in the family Nymphalidae .
Hose 's palm civet ( Diplogale hosei ) , also known as Hose 's civet , is a civet species endemic to the island of Borneo .
Crystallaria is a genus of darters in the family Percidae found in the Mississippi River basin from Ohio to Minnesota and in southern Mississippi , northern Louisiana , and southeastern Oklahoma , and on the Gulf Slope of Escambia , Mobile Bay , and the Pearl River drainages .
The Neotropical fruit bats ( Artibeus ) are a genus of bats within the subfamily Stenodermatinae .
Hylotrupini is a tribe of beetles in the subfamily Cerambycinae , containing the single genus Hylotrupes and the single species Hylotrupes bajulus .
Caryophyllia is a genus of solitary corals in the family Caryophylliidae .
Electrostephanus is an extinct genus of crown wasp in the hymenopteran family Stephanidae , and is the only genus placed in the subfamily Electrostephaninae .
The Taiwan wren - babbler or Taiwan cupwing , ( Pnoepyga formosana ) , is a species of passerine bird in its own family , Pnoepygidae .
Gallimimus was assigned to the Ornithomimidae in 1972 .
Distichodus is a genus of fish in the Distichodontidae family found in tropical Africa .
Humphrey 's caecilian , Ichthyophis humphreyi , is a species of caecilian found presumably in tropical Asia .
Besuchetia ceylanica is a species of beetle in the family Latridiidae , the only species in the genus Besuchetia .
In taxonomy , the Chaetophoraceae are a family of green algae , specifically of the order Chaetophorales .
Eurydictyon conspicuum is a species of beetle in the family Ommatidae , the only species in the genus Eurydictyon .
Striped ground squirrels ( genus Lariscus ) form a taxon of squirrels under the subfamily Callosciurinae .
Distocupes is a monotypic genus of beetles in the family Cupedidae , the reticulated beetles .
Elliottia is a genus of plants in the Ericaceae , with four species , two in North American and two in Japan .
The Borneo shark ( Carcharhinus borneensis ) is a species of requiem shark , and part of the family Carcharhinidae .
Lazarussuchus is the youngest member of the group Choristodera and the only choristodere to have lived after the Eocene .
The Rio Grande shiner ( Notropis jemezanus ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the Cyprinidae family .
The Mount Sinai gecko ( Hemidactylus mindiae ) is a species of lizard in the Gekkonidae family .
Azov shemaya ( Alburnus leobergi ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Alburnus .
Porter 's rock rat ( Aconaemys porteri ) is a species of rodent in the family Octodontidae .
The Urocordylidae belong to a group within the Lepospondyli called the Nectridea , which include forms with long tails and short bodies .
Bank myna ( Acridotheres ginginianus ) , called `` Sharak '' in Punjabi , is a myna found in South Asia .
Ophidiella is a subgenus of the genus Plasmodium created in 1966 by Garnham .
The Natricinae are a subfamily of the Colubridae family of snakes , which comprises 28 genera .
Syringa ( Lilac ) is a genus of 12 currently recognized species of flowering woody plants in the olive family ( Oleaceae ) , native to woodland and scrub from southeastern Europe to eastern Asia , and widely and commonly cultivated in temperate areas elsewhere .
The California kingsnake ( Lampropeltis getula californiae ) is a nonvenomous colubrid snake endemic to the western United States and northern Mexico .
In taxonomy , the Korarchaeota are a phylum of the Archaea .
Cercyonis is a genus of butterflies of the subfamily Satyrinae , commonly called wood - nymphs or wood nymphs in the family Nymphalidae found in North America .
Funchalia is a genus of deep - water prawns of the family Penaeidae .
Mysorelloides multisulcata is a species of tropical freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Paludomidae .
The El Cusuco salamander ( Bolitoglossa diaphora ) is a species of salamander in the family Plethodontidae .
The subfamily Spiraeoideae was traditionally a subfamily of flowering plants within family Rosaceae .
Gallardosaurus was a pliosaurid , a member of the family Pliosauridae , a group of short - necked reptiles that lived during the Mesozoic Era .
Smithatris is a new genus of the ginger family ( Zingiberaceae ) .
The Rio Suno antwren ( Myrmotherula sunensis ) is a species of bird in the family Thamnophilidae .
Anthurium ( /ænˈθjuːriəm/ ; Schott , 1829 ) , is a genus of about 1000 species of flowering plants , the largest genus of the arum family , Araceae .
Gladiolus ( from Latin , the diminutive of gladius , a sword ) is a genus of perennial cormous flowering plants in the iris family ( Iridaceae ) .
Numerous plants , mainly Acanthaceae , are former members of Ruellia .
Helicteroideae is a subfamily of the Malvaceae family .
Whether or not this is the case , Sinraptor and Yangchuanosaurus were close relatives , and are classified together in the family Metriacanthosauridae .
The Senegalese ladyfish , Elops senegalensis , is a species of fish in the Elopidae family , and is native to the coastal waters of the eastern Atlantic Ocean from Mauritania to the Democratic Republic of the Congo .
Jenkinidae is a family of the order Leucosolenida .
Cyanagraea praedator is `` by far the largest '' species in the family Bythograeidae , growing to a maximum carapace size of 123.0 mm × 74.8 mm ( 4.84 in × 2.94 in ) .
Homoranthus is a genus of shrub in the myrtle family Myrtaceae described as a genus in 1836 .
Azara 's night monkey ( Aotus azarae ) , also known as the southern night monkey , is a night monkey species from South America .
Griphomyia is a genus of fruit fly in the family Tephritidae .
The West African black turtle ( Pelusios niger ) is a species of turtle in the Pelomedusidae family .
Salinator is a genus of small , air - breathing , terrestrial or semi - marine snails with an operculum , pulmonate gastropod molluscs in the family Amphibolidae .
Isoetales , formerly also written Isoëtales , is an order of plants in the class Isoetopsida .
Arterivirus is the only genus of viruses in the family Arteriviridae , which is within the order Nidovirales .
Amomyrtella irregularis ( formerly Myrcianthes irregularis ) is a species of tree in the myrtle family , Myrtaceae .
The Saint Helena earwig or Saint Helena giant earwig ( Labidura herculeana ) was a species of earwig endemic to the oceanic island of Saint Helena in the south Atlantic Ocean .
Heikegani ( 平家蟹 , ヘイケガニ ) ( Heikeopsis japonica ) is a species of crab native to Japan , with a shell that bears a pattern resembling a human face which many believed to be the face of an angry samurai hence the nickname Samurai Crab .
The Tufted duck ( Aythya fuligula ) is a small diving duck with a population of close to one million birds .
Naesiotus is a genus of tropical air - breathing land snails , a pulmonate gastropod mollusks in the family Bulimulidae .
Saitoella is a genus of two species of yeast in the family Protomycetaceae .
Comitas is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Turridae , the turrids .
Trapezitinae is a subfamily of the Hesperiidae ( `` skippers '' ) family of butterflies .
The Arfak rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia arfakensis ) is a species of fish in the Melanotaeniidae family .
A palpigrade , commonly known as a microwhip scorpion , is an invertebrate animal belonging to the order Palpigradi in the class Arachnida , in the subphylum Chelicerata of the phylum Arthropoda .
The Sri Lanka bush warbler , Ceylon bush warbler or Palliser 's warbler ( Elaphrornis palliseri ) is an Old World warbler which is an endemic resident breeder in Sri Lanka , where it is the only bush warbler .
Oligobuninae is an extinct subfamily of the family Mustelidae .
Merriam 's pocket gopher ( Cratogeomys merriami ) is a species of rodent in the family Geomyidae .
The Anchieta 's cobra ( Naja anchietae ) , also called the Angolan cobra is a species of cobra in the Elapidae family ; it is native to the southern regions of Africa .
Panarica is a genus in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) and contains 6 species .
Spider monkeys of the genus Ateles are New World monkeys in the subfamily Atelinae , family Atelidae .
The Jamaican blackbird ( Nesopsar nigerrimus ) is a species of bird in the New World blackbird and oriole family Icteridae .
Magnistipula is a genus of plant in family Chrysobalanaceae described as a genus in 1905 .

Garra dembeensis ( the Dembea stone lapper or Cameroon logsucker ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Garra .
Myiagra is a genus of passerine birds in family Monarchidae , the monarch flycatchers , sometimes referred to as the broad - billed flycatchers or simply broadbills ( not to be confused with the broadbills of the family Eurylaimidae ) .

Luigi Pichler ( January 31 , 1773 in Rome -- March 13 , 1854 in Rome ) was a German - Italian artist in engraved gems .
Gaston - François de Witte ( 12 June 1897 , Antwerp -- 1 June 1980 , Brussels ) was a Belgian herpetologist who discovered and described at least 24 different species of reptiles .
Martial Bourdin ( 1868 - -1894 ) was a French anarchist , who died on 15 February 1894 when chemical explosives that he was carrying prematurely detonated outside the Royal Observatory in Greenwich Park .
Anne Spoerry died in 1999 , age 80 , after a stroke in Nairobi ; she was buried on the island of Lamu .
Jerzy Nowosielski ( January 7 , 1923 -- February 21 , 2011 ) was a Kraków - born Polish painter , graphic artist , scenographer , and illustrator .
George Whitman ( December 12 , 1913 -- December 14 , 2011 ) was the proprietor of the Shakespeare and Company bookstore in Paris , which continues to be a popular tourist attraction .
Marie Ernestine Lavieille ( or Marie Lavieille ) ( October 11 , 1852 in Barbizon -- November 12 , 1937 in Le Mans ) was a French painter .

Born in Munich , Günther Alois Friedrich Blumentritt was the son of Günther Blumentritt ( born 23 June 1859 ) , town planner and a Privy Councilor in Munich and Lina Rückart ( born 24 March 1868 ) .
August Rohling ( 15 February 1839 at Neuenkirchen , Province of Westphalia , Prussia -- 23 January 1931 in Salzburg ) was a German Catholic theologian , student of anti - Semitic texts , and polemical author .
Domenico Mondo ( 1734 in Capodrise near Caserta -- 1806 in Naples ) was an Italian painter , active in both a late Baroque and Neoclassical styles .
Ida Roland ( * 18 February 1881 in Vienna ; † 27 March 1951 in Nyon , Switzerland ) , born Ida Klausner , was an Austrian and German actress .

Michel - Dimitri Calvocoressi ( 2 October 1877 in Marseille , France -- 1 February 1944 in London , England ) was a multilingual music writer and critic who promoted musicians such as Franz Liszt and Modest Mussorgsky .

Giuseppe Badaracco ( 1588 - -1657 ) , also called `` Il Sordo '' ( the Deaf ) , was an Italian painter of the Baroque period , active mainly in Genoa , in Liguria and in the island of Corsica .

Guillaume Coustou the Elder ( November 29 , 1677 , Lyon - February 22 , 1746 , Paris ) was a French sculptor and academician .
Paolo Magretti ( 15 December 1854 , Milan -- 30 August 1913 , Paderno Dugnano ) was an Italian entomologist who specialized in Hymenoptera studies .

Francisco Salamone ( June 5 , 1897 -- August 8 , 1959 ) was an Argentine architect of Italian descent who , between 1936 and 1940 , during the Infamous Decade , built more than 60 municipal buildings with elements of Art Deco style in 25 rural communities on the Argentine Pampas within the Buenos Aires Province .

Robert Villemain ( January 10 , 1924 in Paris , France - September 4 , 1984 in Montfermeil , France ) was a French boxer .
